body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

` ./yosys -p "proc; opt; wreduce; simplemap; muxcover; dump" mux_if_bal_3_1.v`

```
module mux_if_bal_3_1 #(parameter N=3, parameter W=1) (input [N*W-1:0] i, input [$clog2(N)-1:0] s, output reg [W-1:0] o);
always @* begin
    o <= {{W{{1'bx}}}};
    if (s[0] == 1'b0)
     if (s[1] == 1'b0)
      o <= i[0*W+:W];
     else
      o <= i[1*W+:W];
    else
     if (s[1] == 1'b0)
      o <= i[2*W+:W];
end
endmodule
```

## Expected behavior

Pack into `$_MUX4_`

## Actual behavior

No packeroonies.

Before `wreduce`:
![before](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6740044/60113502-c0296300-9726-11e9-96a6-7610f84c343f.png)

After `wreduce`:
![after](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6740044/60113518-c61f4400-9726-11e9-9092-db58672b76e4.png)

